  "body": "### Description\n\nWhen adding `quarkus-grpc` extension as dependency, it pulls `vertx` and `vertx-web` extensions which are overhead for simple applications or projects which don't use WEB at all so Quarkus shouldn't bind and listen to HTTP ports. When someone is using the gRPC extension, it shouldn't assume that WEB is also used. \n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nThe HTTP server should be optional as it is used only for DevUI. This `<!-- for dev mode, TODO: try to get rid of it-->` is present as a comment to the pom.xml of `quarkus-grpc` extension. ",
